fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars.histories

Class LeastSquaresInterpolatorGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars.histories.LeastSquaresInterpolatorGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IncrementalInterpolatorGeneratorI

    public class LeastSquaresInterpolatorGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements IncrementalInterpolatorGeneratorI
    The class LeastSquaresInterpolatorGenerator implements interpolators based on a least squares approach, producing polynomials of orders 1, 2 or 3 and able to manage a limited (in size) window of values.

    Description

    This implementation uses the Apache common-math library to compute the least squares polynomials. Hence, the polynomials are recomputed anew each time a new point is added to the function. Therefore, this implementation is relatively inefficient both computationally, as the least squares computation is redone from scratch repetitively, and in terms of memory as it requires to embark the common-math library.

    Glass-box Invariants

     invariant       windowSize >= 2
 invariant       obs != null

    Black-box Invariants

     invariant       getOrder() > 0 && getOrder() <= 3

    Created on : 2022-07-13

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
